# Code ownership rules for the public template catalog.
#
# Gen0Sec-curated content (system tier) is shipped pre-installed for
# every tenant and lives at templates/system/. Community submissions
# (custom tier) live at templates/custom/ and require maintainer
# review but are not pre-installed.
#
# The branch ruleset on `main` requires Code Owner review (see
# `gh api repos/gen0sec/workflow-templates/rulesets`), so the paths
# listed below cannot merge without an approving review from a member
# of @gen0sec/developers — even if a regular reviewer has already
# approved the PR.

# Default: any maintainer can approve community PRs touching custom/
# templates or docs.
*                           @gen0sec/developers

# System tier — Gen0Sec-curated. The branch ruleset enforces Code
# Owner review on these paths.
/templates/system/          @gen0sec/developers

# Build + sync plumbing — protected to keep the R2 publish path
# trusted. A compromised CI script could ship arbitrary content
# under any tier.
/scripts/                   @gen0sec/developers
/.github/                   @gen0sec/developers
